pyBMI is very small library that prints the Body mass index of a person 
it uses the S.I. (system international ) metrics kg and cm (or meters)
if your really want something in other metrics your are free to change it 
for your needs.


giving a how tall (in cm or meters ) and how heavy (in kg ) someone is 
it tells  what classification he/she belongs 
it also tells how much kg somebody should lose to be Normal (if he/she is fat )
It currently follows the rules according to 
http://apps.who.int/bmi/index.jsp?introPage=intro_3.html




